Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner stuffed
Over one third of children aged 9-13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and 5% obesity.
Obese children come from most of their families with a lifestyle that is not healthy, according to current research.
The importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference, is demonstrated again.
At the table, obsessive children, for example, are fed of embites at least twice as often as children in families with normal weight.
