In overweight families there is no custom of practicing sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of the last school year and nearly 900 basic education children from all over Chechnya participated in the same.
It was already the second edition of the program "The obesity of is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
A proper diet and exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly decrease the number of overweight and even obesity children.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five daily meals according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast but ink for dinner
Experts warn that, in a healthy development, details are also important, which they also count, such as having a fixed time for family breakfast.
In Czechia, however, only 23 per cent of schoolchildren's families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one breakfast alone.
But the worst was to discover that in 10% of households there was nothing breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children, cold potatoes are often consumed more frequently.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink sweet drinks daily (70%).
Generally, they make sport more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years, from the point of view of healthy food, are far from ideal."
Among its favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"The popularity of sweet refreshments is above all alarming," the final report of the study states.
As the main food, the palm takes the pasta and follows it closely with the meat of the bird.
Practically, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Switching to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who completed the questionnaire after completing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence," a significant change was made in many cases in favour of the principles of healthy diet," points out the results of the study.
He draws attention, for example, to sweet refreshments, where many children would begin to prefer ordinary water.
Children would also more often choose poultry and fish meat for the main meal in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
