In Need for Speed: The Run competes throughout America.
Review
A trip, in principle neglected, is complicated because of a number of improper neglects of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but this was of no use if, in fact, nothing was meant to be done extraordinary.
The new delivery, to which the title is added The Run, aroused great expectations already before its premiere.
I promised that I would give new air to the old racer Need for Speed and, as shown, appears as a game that should not end up being a genre of action again without more.
We also feel curious about how the scenes would be inserted, where the main character descends from the car and walks by his own foot.
As often happens in the NFS series, the results don't vary much in terms of what we expected.
There are careers that can be made for acceptable, but in the total calculation points are lost due to absurd errors, which have been appearing in the series for years.
In reality, mistakes cannot be called, but they are rather the incomprehensible disadvantage of programmers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist Jack has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one does not have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasant to the sight, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
So it's nothing from the other world.
But walking through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, careers are sometimes diversified by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance a number of required rivals (the usual in a classic race), then try to make time (the classic timed duel) and then wait for a duel against a single opponent.
In the middle of all of this, the police sometimes appear, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are quite fewer landscapes in the game of what might be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that makes the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the tracks of previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with a lot of action is quite suitable for this driving style, although we can find something better among the games of competition.
So far, everything's in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
Of games like this you can't expect to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a hit on any object, you can't predict how your car will react, which is not all in order.
It is typical that, by making a very adjusted advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
It even ends up completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reseteo system, there are no great problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five recipes are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just a help in case something isn't right, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, nor reseteo helps, only helps him learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, one must enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Sometimes you'll find yourselves in some "civil" vehicle site with the same configuration, even if you're the first, fifth, or you'll be five minutes before or after.
This makes anger especially in situations, when you see two cars going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or stop.
It's the same when you arrive, because it's programmed that the "surprise" will always happen before your noses.
Opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the trip you will reach places where, without taking into account the moment, you will always advance the same opponent on the same site.
Moreover, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming in front of you, so at first you can make the car paper.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you are likely to be disappointed immediately.
And it's a shame, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it's often not possible to follow the detail what happens or where.
And it really looks the same, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive clues or ranking in the race so that it doesn't get bored, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during racing.
You have to be aware of the gas stationers next to the road, because that's exactly where you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough of what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, for strong American cars for straight highways and for super-deportive exotics for technical driving, for example by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, i.e., there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both the challenges and the stories.
At the top level, the driver is opened up several possibilities, starting with the car and finishing with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an Autolog feature is connected online, comparing your results with that of other players and making other community functions available.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race is made in history.
With the car you reach the metro tunnel (pass), where you run dark through the roads (pass).
The Velocimeter marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (passe) and, suddenly, the metro convoy arrives behind you and you are carried forward without more.
In the writing we will probably have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the game programming no one thought even a little or if the authors actually take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
For what a shame it is that, at the most tense times, the quality of the image is reduced and, at times, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a question of taste.
In order to be pleased with most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each one of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is thus quite confusing.
If the game were to avoid absolutely foolish mistakes, we would have trouble asserting that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It feels like the game isn't over.
Fun is assured, but be prepared because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of some airport reflectors.
The choirs of the University of Carolina will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Third World Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
During the same period, twenty corals of high school and university centres will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"The University of Carolina has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee is the rector Václav Hampl", said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance for all audiences to the high school choir concert, which will be held on 17 March at 14 hours before the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program has the participation of Czech jazzist Karel R .žička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening will be held at the town halls in Vynohrady the concert "Tirciopelo Students", in which university choirs will participate, including the choir of the University of Carolina.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Student Day with dignity and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Terciopel Revolution, but also to present coral music to the public at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Union of Corals in collaboration with the Instituto de Secundaria Jan Kepler.
All the acts were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebrative concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised shows of students and morning concerts.
Interested people will be able to find more information on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
