The innovative IBM begins its second century of existence
If someone was looking for a term that clearly defined IBM's strategy, the closest term would be "long term".
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and, however, has already been a hundred years since its foundation.
The basis of this long-lasting character placed the first head of the firm, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He already coined the motto that many problems in the world have solutions if people are willing to think.
His slogan "Think!" became his seal, around which he will build the life of the giant future (it was also the title of an internal magazine that IBM began to publish in 1935).
